Algorithm 1 CSGN   
Input: A noisy dataset $\tilde{\mathcal{D}}$ , Warm Up epoch $T_{w}$ , Total epoch $T_{m a x}$ . .   
1: $g_{Y}^{1},g_{Y}^{2}\leftarrow\mathrm{WarmUP}(\tilde{D})$ ;   
2: For $\mathrm{T}=1,\hdots,T_{w}$ :   
3: For ${\bf k}\!\!=\!1$ , 2:   
4: Sample $(\pmb{x},\tilde{y})\sim\tilde{D}$ ;   
5: $\hat{y}\leftarrow\pmb{g}_{Y}^{k}(\pmb{x})$ ;   
6: Sample $(z,s)\sim q_{\phi}^{k}(Z,S|X=x,Y=\hat{y})$ ;   
7: Calculate the prior distribution $p_{W,\pmb{\mu}_{N},\pmb{\sigma}_{N}^{2}}^{k}(Z|Y=\hat{y})$ based on $\hat{y}$ ;   
8: Sample $\hat{\pmb{x}}\sim p_{\pmb{f}_{X}}^{k}(X|Z=M_{X}\odot z,S=s)$ ;   
9: Sample $\hat{\tilde{y}}\sim p_{\pmb{f}_{\tilde{Y}}}^{k}\left(\tilde{Y}\vert\pmb{Z}=M_{\tilde{Y}}\odot\pmb{z}\right)$ ;   
10: Calculate the loss using Eq. (5) and update networks $q_{\phi}^{k}(\cdot),p_{W,\mu_{N},\sigma_{N}^{2}}^{k}(\cdot),p_{f_{X}}^{k}(\cdot)$ and $p_{f_{\tilde{Y}}}^{k}(\cdot)$ ;   
11: For $\mathrm{T}=1,\dots,T_{m a x}$ :   
12: $S_{X},S_{U}\gets\mathrm{Selection}(\tilde{\mathcal{D}},g_{Y}^{1},g_{Y}^{2})$ ;   
13: $S_{X}^{\prime},S_{U}^{\prime}\leftarrow\mathrm{MixUp}(S_{X},S_{U})$ ;   
14: For $k{=}1,2$ :   
15: Sample $(\pmb{x},\tilde{y})\sim\tilde{D}$ ;   
16: $\hat{y}\leftarrow\pmb{g}_{Y}^{k}(\pmb{x})$ ;   
17: Sample $(z,s)\sim q_{\phi}^{k}(Z,S|X=x,Y=\hat{y})$ ;   
18: Calculate the prior distribution $p_{W,\pmb{\mu}_{N},\pmb{\sigma}_{N}^{2}}^{k}(Z|Y=\hat{y})$ based on $\hat{y}$ ;   
19: Sample $\hat{\pmb{x}}\sim p_{\pmb{f}_{X}}^{k}(X|Z=M_{X}\odot z,S=s)$ ;   
20: Sample $\hat{\tilde{y}}\sim p_{f_{\tilde{Y}}}^{k}\left(\tilde{Y}\vert Z=M_{\tilde{Y}}\odot z\right)$ ;   
21: Calculate the loss using Eq. (5) and update networks $g_{Y}^{k}(\cdot),q_{\phi}^{k}(\cdot),p_{W,\mu_{N},\sigma_{N}^{2}}^{k}(\cdot),p_{f_{X}}^{k}(\cdot)$ and   
$p_{f_{\bar{Y}}}^{k}(\cdot);$   
Output: The classification networks $g_{Y}^{1},g_{Y}^{2}$ .
